  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Folder</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1951 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The folder features a collage of two images. The circular image in the centre of the page shows the faces of a middle-aged couple. The man’s lips are brushing the woman’s left cheek. He is looking at her, while she is looking away. She has dark hair and a stud earring in her right ear. The man has fairer hair. Above this picture, another image shows six armed soldiers in uniform. Three are lined up on the left, the other three on the right in other uniforms. The latter are of Asian origin. All six men are looking towards the camera, smiling. The Serbo-Croatian translation of the English original film title ‘Go for broke!’ is printed across the lower part of the folder: ‘Sve ili ništa’ (All or nothing).</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The number ‘4’ noted in handwriting on the top right corner is probably an outdated registration number. The film was directed by Robert Pirosh and released in 1951.</ab>
